ncil Speech<\/em><a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/3UopMzX\">\u200b\u200b\u200b<\/a><em><\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200bII.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Psychiatrist <strong>Thomas Szasz<\/strong> on what is required to learn:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;Every act of conscious learning requires the willingness to suffer an injury to one&#8217;s self-esteem. That is why young children, before they are aware of their own self-importance, learn so easily; and why older persons, especially if vain or important, cannot learn at all.&#8221;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Source: <\/em><a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/4k615DM\">\u200b<em>Words to the Wise<\/em>\u200b<\/a><em> (hat tip to <\/em><a href=\"https:\/\/x.com\/dylanoa4\">\u200b<em>Dylan O&#8217;Sullivan<\/em>\u200b<\/a><em>)<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-1-question-for-you\">1 QUESTION FOR YOU<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A question from entrepreneur <strong>Nathan Barry<\/strong> on patience:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;When does it benefit me to be patient and when does it not?&#8221;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Until next week,<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>James Clear <a href=\"https:\/\/jamesclear.com\/atomic-habits\">\u200b\u200b\u200b<\/a> <br><em>Author of <\/em><a href=\"https:\/\/jamesclear.com\/atomic-habits\">\u200b<em>Atomic Habits<\/em>\u200b<\/a><em> <\/em><br><em>Creator of the <\/em><a href=\"https:\/\/jamesclear.com\/3-2-1\">\u200b<em>3-2-1 Newsletter<\/em>\u200b<\/a><em> <\/em><br><em>Founding Author of <\/em><a href=\"https:\/\/authorsequity.com\/\">\u200b<em>Authors Equity<\/em>\u200b<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>p.s. \u200b<a href=\"https:\/\/jamesclear.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/Screenshot-2025-02-20-at-1.31.00\u202fPM.png\">Seems like a fair trade<\/a>\u200b.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>3 IDEAS FROM ME I. &#8220;S